*Workaround*
Power Off the VM from vSphere, the instance will be marked as terminated as expected.

comments.body:
Thanks, [~mclark]! I am seeing a couple problems in that output, perhaps related to the main problem (instances stuck in shutting-down) or perhaps not.

* There is a message formatting problem somewhere: {code}null value for element "{http://eucalyptus.ucsb.edu/}migrationCapable"{code} and {code}NULL parameter was passed when a non NULL parameter was expected{code}
* Somehow, the {{.5.60}} node got removed from {{resourceCache[]}} on CC even though it has instances running on it. That's a bug, as the log states. I suspect that when I added this check, I covered the case of a node being removed from the {{NODES}} line in the config file, but not the case of a node being removed due to being unresponsive, which is what happens here.
